🎁 Gift Idea: bring new life to treasured old photos! It’s EASY - no need for a scanner. Simply use your smartphone to snap a pic of your archival image. The rules:

1. Use painters tape to keep the edges flat while you take the photo.
2. Take the photo outdoors in a shaded area midday when there’s lots of bright light.
3. Youse your iPhone photo app to straighten and crop before you upload 

Such an amazing way to honor cherished photographs from the past. Frame. Travel Print for your parents of a favorite childhood trip.

Merry Christmas to our online family. Thank you for making our dreams come true. We thought we might lose our business during the pandemic but YOU showed up. We are so overwhelmed with gratitude.

@tiffpena @edynmarie

In case you were wondering ♥️ We are a team of five, working each day, and often into the night, to make a product that you find both beautiful and meaningful.

Our home base is in Huntington Beach, California. As Mom’s, we know that our personal photos are our most prized possession and as artists, we know that design matters. With incredible enthusiasm, we hope to create more and more products you grow to love and that celebrate your beautiful lives ✨

Happy New Year

Thinking about framing your print yourself? We’ve chosen to produce prints in a standardized size so that our customers can opt for sprucing their own frames.

Our signature giclée art prints are produced with premium, museum-quality FSC-certified, acid-free, paper — highly resistant to aging. Our matte 230gsm paper has a smooth, neutral-white finish.

If you order your print unframed it will arrive unmounted shipped flat in a reinforced sleeve.

If you doooooo decide to frame with us, you won’t regret it. Our custom frames are hand crafted and assembled in the USA, made with premium materials and are archival, guaranteed not to warp or discolor over time. ✨✨✨
